All Classes

Class Description
AbstractInstructionFactory
Base interface for RegisterInstructionFactory, ImmediateInstructionFactory, and JumpInstructionFactory.
Computer
Computer is the base class for the MIPS simulation and is responsible for the following tasks: Initialization of data memory and management of memory.
ComputerInstance
ComputerInstance is a puppeteering class that prevents instantiation of the Computer class when utilized as a Singleton design pattern.
ComputerTest
Test class for Computer and ComputerInstance classes.
ImmediateInstruction
The base class for immediate instruction representation in MIPS.
ImmediateInstructionFactory
Factory pattern-based class for ImmediateInstruction objects.
ImmediateInstructionTest
Test class for the ImmediateInstruction class.
Instruction
The base interface for RegisterInstruction, ImmediateInstruction, and JumpInstruction.
InstructionFactory
Delegates the object creation of RegisterInstruction, ImmediateInstruction, and JumpInstruction based on the given InstructionString object data.
InstructionFactoryTest
Test class for the InstructionFactory class.
InstructionString
The container class for binary string data.
InstructionStringTest
Test class for the InstructionString class.
JumpInstruction
The base class for jump instruction representation in MIPS.
JumpInstructionFactory
Factory pattern-based class for JumpInstruction objects.
JumpInstructionTest
Test class for the JumpInstruction class
RegisterInstruction
The base class for register instruction representation in MIPS.
RegisterInstructionFactory
Factory pattern-based class for RegisterInstruction objects.
RegisterInstructionTest
Test class for the RegisterInstruction class.
Simulator
Driver class that instantiates a MIPS simulator and an instruction loader (ROM BIOS).
